-how to install claude code on terminal
- verify the installation
authenticate it with your anthropic account


Prerequisites:
1)active anthropic account
2)  git installed for windows users - claude code uses git bash internally.

1)Git for windows  search ---download the installer --once complete git bash is available===

first open windows powershell in your system. either powrhell or cmd for our setup 
Claude code is installed through npm . You need Node.js and npm available in your machine

c:windows/system32> winget install OpenJS.NodeJS
This installs the latest NodeJS version.
check node.js and npm installed correctly
c:\windows\system32> node -v

C:\windows\system32> npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code
This installs claude code globally so you can use claude code from anywhere in the terminal

once installation finishes, you can launch claude code from the terminal.
Claude code is designed to work directly in the terminal and help with the designing tasks.

























